llows from the Poisson summation formula and periodic gauge. Using the Fourier transformed\n\npotential V\u2113\u2113\u2032(r) =1\n\nqNP\n\nq\u2208EBZe\u2212iq\u00b7rV\u2113\u2113\u2032(q), the interaction then takes the form\n\n\u02c6V=X\n\n\u2113\u2113\u2032X\n\nq\u2208EBZV\u2113\u2113\u2032(q) : \u02c6\u03c1q\u2113\u02c6\u03c1\u2212q\u2113\u2032: (C7)\n\nwhere colons denote normal ordering with respect to the vacuum.", "embedding": [-0.0001947573, -0.021403737, 0.041601222, -0.0075586713, 0.0066478066, -0.002616169, -0.0031194005, -0.03635878, -0.06551684, 0.07006292, 0.042348895, -0.0040928046, 0.03450773, -0.054259516, -0.0076830382, 0.024197266, -0.0065412726, -0.020100322, -0.062241007, 0.0015725003, 0.02462454, -0.0072302297, -0.056600634, -0.03416809, -0.02531865, 0.028073194, 0.008831679, 0.009982693, 0.062285963, 0.040841267, 0.048285645, -0.053673528, 0.009609736, -0.056598935, -0.020926053, -0.0020169406, -0.019005552, -0.011286846, 0.028425679, -0.014660021, 0.05993788, -0.007813293, -0.01627289, -0.009181479, -0.011380154, -0.013545743, -0.03081205, -0.009853349, -0.03637342, -0.07960806, 0.01449964, 0.00777793, 0.04135864, -0.010563257, -0.031804115, 0.012602394, -0.019556459, -0.015231005, -0.0013922165, -0.004321731, 0.015146799, -0.023049109, -0.007967408, -0.04644455, 0.0037879446, 0.03697219, -0.017116908, 0.093597695, -0.0050170757, -0.028161136, 0.0039874455, -0.018620564, -0.045535676, 0.015683353, -0.039081704, 0.00522871, -0.019947154, -0.03445212, -0.07019807, -0.00446486, -0.021856122, -0.029736014, -0.0060046166, 0.01261844, -0.012439567, -0.02656659, -0.019687934, -0.02933193, -0.000600759, 0.023496995, 0.035866503, 0.06891365, -0.006108448, -0.03195466, 0.008543888, 0.046797257, 0.0058697867, 0.024747321, 0.012302332, 0.0007414206, 0.03321383, 0.05359697, -0.032784402, 0.043088347, -0.031562224, 0.057230942, -0.007515415, 0.0018102076, 0.020650232, -0.040344898, 0.018237934, -0.011836584, 0.010068603, 0.018961068, 0.00779809, 0.0144489